# Implementation Plan - Phase 2 (Execution)

## 🛠 Tech Stack Recommendation
- **Frontend**: Next.js (App Router) + Tailwind CSS + Shadcn UI (Modern, mobile-friendly)
- **Backend/Storage**: Google Sheets API (via `google-spreadsheet` npm package)
- **Image Hosting**: Cloudinary or Imgur API (for easy image handling)
- **Deployment**: Vercel (Quick & free tier available)

## 📝 Step-by-Step Execution

### Step 1: Project Setup
- [ ] Initialize Next.js project in `proxy-shopping-app/`
- [ ] Configure Google Cloud Service Account & obtain credentials
- [ ] Setup a Google Sheet with the 3 tabs defined in `info.md`

### Step 2: Data Access Layer
- [ ] Create `lib/google-sheets.ts` to handle CRUD operations
- [ ] Implement `getCustomers`, `getItemsByCustomer`, `addPayment` functions

### Step 3: Core UI Components
- [ ] **Dashboard**: Table/List of customers with their net balance (highlighted)
- [ ] **Item Entry**: Form with JPY, Rate, and File Upload (Cloudinary integration)
- [ ] **Transaction History**: Combined view of items and payments for a specific customer

### Step 4: Logic & Calculation
- [ ] Implement the "Outstanding Balance" formula in the frontend state
- [ ] Add simple currency conversion helper (JPY -> HKD based on item-specific rate)

## 🧪 Verification Plan
- [ ] Add a test item and verify it appears in the Google Sheet
- [ ] Record a partial payment and ensure the dashboard balance updates correctly
- [ ] Test image upload and display on the customer detail page
